{
  "texts": [
    "A.1 EXPERIMENT SETUP For the MNIST dataset, we employ a four-layer CNN, consisting of two convolutional layers followed by two fully connected layers, as described in Robey et al. (2022).",
    "For the CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100, CINIC-10 and SVHN datasets, we independently train VGG-19, ResNet-18, and WideResNet-28-10 on each dataset, and additionally include Vision Transformer (ViT) and Data-efficient Image Transformer (Deit) for CIFAR-10.",
    "For the TinyImageNet dataset, we train ResNet-18 and ResNet-34 using the same training configuration as for CIFAR-10.",
    "For the ImageNet-50 dataset, we train a ResNet-18 model separately.",
    "All models are trained using stochastic gradient descent (SGD) with a momentum of 0.9 and a weight decay coefficient of 3.5 × 10 -3."
  ]
}